cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper deals with anomaly detection in 802.11 wireless networks, which falls under the category of network security and network performance analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as Hidden Markov Model (HMM) and Universal Background Model (UBM), which are used for anomaly detection, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The paper also involves simulation using OMNeT++/INET network simulator, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Systems and Control). The use of machine learning techniques also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
